article.headline: Canisius 75, Loyola, Md. 58
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Greg Logins scored 26 points, going 8 of 10 from 3-point range, to lead Canisius over Loyola (Md.) 75-58 on Sunday in the regular-season finale for both teams. The Golden Griffins (15-14, 9-9 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) trailed by as many as 11 points in the first half but cut it to six, 32-26, at halftime. Canisius then scored eight of the first 10 points of the second half to tie it at 34 on Logins' 3-pointer with 16:30 to play. The Greyhounds (15-14, 10-8) went back on top, 40-39, less than 2 minutes later, but wouldn't lead the rest of the way. Another Logins' 3-pointer put the Golden Griffins up for good, 45-42, with 11:59 remaining. Elton Frazier added 18 points for Canisius, which earned the sixth seed and a first-round bye in the conference tournament. It's the first bye for Canisius since 1999. Rudolph had 14 points and 10 rebounds for Loyola.
